HEADWORD: Aponeurosis
<hw>Ap`o*neu*ro"sis</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Aponeuroses</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[Gr.
<?/, fr. <?/ to pass into a tendon; <?/ from + <?/ to strain the sinews,
<?/ sinew, tendon, nerve.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Any one of the
thicker and denser of the deep fasci⟦ae⟧ which cover, invest, and the
terminations and attachments of, many muscles. They often differ from
tendons only in being flat and thin. See <er>Fascia</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
